President Cyril Ramaphosa will officially open Vedanta Zinc International’s Gamsberg mine in South Africa’s Northern Cape Province today. He will be joined by Minister of Mineral Resources, Gwede Mantashe, and Northern Cape Premier, Sylvia Lucas. The Presidential delegation will be hosted by Vedanta Chairman, Anil Agarwal, Vedanta CEO, Srinivasan Venkatakrishnan, and Vedanta Zinc International CEO, Deshnee Naidoo. A live-stream of the proceedings is available at https://bit.ly/2T69wGn from 10h00.